---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "diodes — ecute.club";
---
<BaseLayout {title}>
  <article class="container">
    <h1>diodes</h1>
    <p><strong>what is a diode?</strong> a one-way valve for current. when forward-biased it conducts with a small voltage drop; reversed, it (mostly) blocks.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      orientation: the <strong>stripe = cathode (−)</strong>. conventional current flows from anode → cathode.
    </div>

    <h2>common kinds</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>signal/rectifier</strong>: general one-way conduction.</li>
      <li><strong>Schottky</strong>: lower drop (~0.2–0.4 V), faster; great for protection.</li>
      <li><strong>Zener</strong>: designed to conduct in reverse at a set voltage (clamps).</li>
      <li><strong>LED</strong>: light-emitting diode (see <a href="/guides/leds">LEDs</a>).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>tiny polarity-protection sketch</h2>
    <div class="diagram" role="img" aria-label="series diode for reverse-polarity protection">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 520 120" width="100%" height="auto">
        <rect x="0" y="0" width="520" height="120" rx="16" fill="var(--card)"/>
        <text x="36" y="64" class="mono">+V</text>
        <line x1="70" y1="60" x2="200" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"/>
        <!-- simple diode body with stripe -->
        <rect x="200" y="50" width="40" height="20" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"/>
        <line x1="232" y1="50" x2="232" y2="70" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"/>
        <text x="210" y="48" class="mono mini">stripe = −</text>
        <line x1="240" y1="60" x2="420" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"/>
        <text x="430" y="64" class="mono">to circuit</text>
        <line x1="40" y1="100" x2="480" y2="100" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="18" y="104" class="mono">0V</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <h2>rules of thumb</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>budget the forward drop in your voltage plan.</li>
      <li>for coils (motors/relays), add a <strong>flyback diode</strong> across the coil (stripe to +).</li>
      <li>use Zeners for simple voltage clamps/reference; mind power dissipation.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>